properties.desc: You stumble across a secret casino once used by the occupants of the tunnels.
You find a hidden library amongst the rooms.
You enter a lavish room, its occupants seemingly comfortable in this strange place.
You find an old armory here, most of the weapons worn by the sands of time

You find what appears to be a full suite. Despite how out of place it is, a senior mercenary would have no trouble living here.
You see an old storage room, filled with armor and other knick-knacks.
You come across an old armor, most of its gear pilfered.
You see what looks to be an old food storage room. Now, only rats come and go.
You enter a long hallway filled with identical rooms. You intuit that there were barracks back from when there were soldiers preparing for war.
You see an altar on the opposite side of the room. Clearly, this was where any worshipping was done back in the day.
You enter a storage locker. There's no such thing as being too prepared.

You look around the room and see pillars, rising to the ceiling, as well as sacrificial pyres and altars.
